ENTRY       EC 1.2.3.9                  Enzyme
NAME        aryl-aldehyde oxidase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
            With oxygen as acceptor
SYSNAME     aryl-aldehyde:oxygen oxidoreductase
REACTION    an aromatic aldehyde + O2 + H2O = an aromatic carboxylate + H2O2 [RN:R01489]
ALL_REAC    R01489 > R05273
SUBSTRATE   aromatic aldehyde [CPD:C00193];
            O2 [CPD:C00007];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     aromatic carboxylate;
            H2O2 [CPD:C00027]
COMMENT     Acts on benzaldehyde, vanillin and a number of other aromatic aldehydes, but not on aliphatic aldehydes or sugars.
HISTORY     EC 1.2.3.9 created 1986, modified 2002
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Crawford, D.L., Sutherland, J.B., Pometto, A.L., III and Miller, J.M.
  TITLE     Production of an aromatic aldehyde oxidase by Streptomyces viridosporus.
  JOURNAL   Arch. Microbiol. 131 (1982) 351-355.
